Name.subject: Lehmann, Heinz E.
Title: Heinz E. Lehmann in 1970
Description.biographicalNote: Heinz E. Lehmann (1911-99) was born and educated in Germany, receiving his MD in 1935 from the University of Berlin. He fled Nazi Germany in 1937, settled in Montreal, Canada, and became the Clinical Director at Verdun Protestant Hospital in 1947. After learning of European work on chlorpromazine, he published the first North American study of that drug in 1954; in 1957, he published the first North American study of imipramine. Lehmann became chair of psychiatry at McGill University in 1970. He served as President of both the ACNP and the CINP.
